Job Description
Under the overall and direct supervision of the Chief of Mission in Islamabad, and in cooperation with relevant units in IOM Islamabad, the successful candidate will be responsible for the following responsibilities. The incumbent will: Coordinate and support
supervision and management of effective and efficient IOM programmes
related to migration management in collaboration with relevant
counterparts in the government and development partners in the countryAnalyse and interpret
trends, challenges and priorities in Pakistan with regard to
migration management interventions and maintain partnerships with national
authorities and institutions working on the same issuesRepresent IOM in
relevant internal/external meetings, working groups and coordination
forums and respond to requests for information on projects.Contribute to
development of and implement awareness raising activities in coordination
with implementing counterparts as requiredEnsure project
implementation and monitor progress of the project by evaluating the
projects together with government counterparts and other partners
keeping the COM informed on the status of implementation of each
projectCoordinate daily
administration of the programme departmentCoordinate with
Government counterparts in relation to IOM’s country programme
implementation/management in the areas of migration management and ensure
results-based programme deliveryEnsure project implementation and evaluate lessons learnt for
further integration into project outlines keeping in view newly developed
policies and good practices and establishing appropriate execution and
monitoring mechanisms and systemsStay up to date regarding assessments and
reports produced by other agencies and organizations and ensure relevant
and important information is incorporated in IOM reports, project
proposals and strategies.Prepare
programme/project status reports required for management, donors, budget
review, programme analysis, annual reports, etc.Liaise with other local
government, International Organizations, national and international
institutions and NGOs, and other members of civil society working on
common issuesSupport IOM resource
mobilization efforts by preparing relevant documentation and participating
in donor meetings and public information eventsSupport and strengthen
IOM’s strategic alliances and partnerships for effective and comprehensive
activities in the area of migration managementOrganize coordination
meetings, workshops, working groups and donor meetings relating to
migration management, within the country and regionally with various
counterparts as per requirementPerform any other
duties assigned by the Chief of Mission Education and Experience: Completed university degree from an accredited academic institution preferably in Social Sciences or related discipline; b) 3 years of experience in projects implementation; c) previous work experience in Central or South Asia, particularly in Pakistan, on similar programming highly advantageous especially as regards to proof of EU Readmission project knowledge/expertise and implementation. Languages:
Thorough knowledge of English & Urdu
